==English==
===Etymology===
Named after French [[chemist]] [[w:Louis Daguerre|Louis Daguerre]] who announced the process in 1839.  Daguerre and [[w:Nicéphore Niépce|Nicéphore Niépce]] had together invented it.
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# An early type of [[photograph]] creating by exposing a silver surface which has previously been exposed to either [[iodine]] or [[bromine]] vapour.
